# Ignore RAG/ contents EXCEPT the converted-markdown knowledge base, which
# is public TEP literature (Downs & Vogel 1993, McAvoy 2003) that the
# agent's search_process_knowledge tool indexes at runtime. Without these
# files in the repo, a fresh clone or Docker build gives the agent an
# empty KB — Dockerfile.backend's `COPY RAG/` would also fail outright,
# as it did on the first v0.3.0 release attempt.
#
# Git can't re-include a child of an excluded directory, so we exclude
# RAG/* (files + immediate subdirs) and then re-include the one subdir
# we want; that subdir's contents then follow normal rules.
RAG/*
!RAG/converted_markdown
# Explicit re-include — one of the KB files happens to be named
# `*_REFERENCE*.md`, which is caught by the global `*_REFERENCE*.md`
# rule further down. Negate it here so the file gets committed.
!RAG/converted_markdown/2_TEP_Complete_Technical_Reference.md
image/
requirements-frozen.txt
*_backup_*.py
*.backup_*
PORTABILITY.md

